# Aucctus Development Rules

## React TypeScript Guidelines

### Components
- Use functional components with hooks instead of class components
- Use arrow functions for component definitions
- Use destructuring for props
- Implement lazy loading and code splitting
- Optimize images and assets
- Use memoization for expensive calculations
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders using useMemo and useCallback

### Security
- Sanitize user input
- Avoid storing sensitive information in local storage
- Use environment variables for sensitive configuration

### Documentation
- Document complex logic with comments
- Document component props with JSDoc
- Document custom hooks with JSDoc

## Styling Guidelines

### Tailwind Best Practices
- Use Aucctus theme classes first, then supplement with Tailwind utilities
- Implement responsive utilities for different screen sizes
- Use animation utilities for transitions
- ALWAYS use the `cn` utility with object notation for conditional classes

### Component Design
- Ensure responsive design using Tailwind's responsive prefixes
- Maintain accessibility with proper color contrast
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide appropriate ARIA attributes
- Support keyboard navigation
- Follow established component patterns for consistency

### Code Quality
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Optimize for performance
- Ensure component accessibility
- Be vigilant about type safety and type inference

### Theme System
- Always use Aucctus theme classes as the primary styling approach
- Below are the theme classes that are available:

## Text Colors
- aucctus-text-primary - Main text color
- aucctus-text-secondary / aucctus-text-secondary-hover - Secondary text color
- aucctus-text-tertiary / aucctus-text-tertiary-hover - Tertiary text color
- aucctus-text-quaternary / aucctus-text-quaternary-hover - Quaternary text color
- aucctus-text-white - White text
- aucctus-text-disabled - Disabled text
- aucctus-text-placeholder / aucctus-text-placeholder-subtle - Placeholder text
- aucctus-text-brand-primary - Primary brand text
- aucctus-text-brand-secondary - Secondary brand text
- aucctus-text-brand-tertiary / aucctus-text-brand-tertiary-alt - Tertiary brand text
- aucctus-text-error-primary - Error text
- aucctus-text-warning-primary - Warning text
- aucctus-text-success-primary - Success text

