## Button Classes
- btn - Base button class
- btn-primary, btn-primary-light, btn-light, btn-grey, btn-secondary, btn-success, btn-danger, btn-warning, btn-info, btn-disabled - Button variants
- btn-xs, btn-sm, btn-md, btn-lg - Button sizes
- btn-bold - Bold text button
- btn-no-border, btn-link - Borderless button styles
- btn-no-hover - Disable hover effects
- example usage: <button className="btn btn-primary">Click me</button>

## Important Notes on Hover Classes
- For classes with "-hover" suffix (like aucctus-bg-primary-hover, aucctus-text-secondary-hover), use them directly in your className
- Do NOT use with the hover: prefix (e.g., use "aucctus-bg-primary-hover" instead of "hover:aucctus-bg-primary")
- No need to include both the base class and hover class - the hover class already includes the base styling
- Example: Use `className="aucctus-bg-primary-hover"` instead of `className="aucctus-bg-primary hover:aucctus-bg-primary-hover"`

  
